license choices may become limited by the licenses of the other works.

Especially, the included Makefile may create works restricted further by
the licenses of the sample sets that were used:

- fluidsynth-ydp: only the CC licenses (choice "c" or "d") may be
  used; credit the author according to
  http://freepats.zenvoid.org/Piano/acoustic-grand-piano.html, of course

- fluidsynth-hsdamped: only the CC licenses (choice "c" or "d") may be
  used; make sure to credit
  [Hispasonic](http://www.hispasonic.com/noticias/dsk-music-presenta-hispasonic-sampled-series/3685)

- fluidsynth-sbelmont: only the CC licenses (choice "c" or "d") may be
  used; make sure to credit
  [SBelmont](https://www.kvraudio.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=452609)

- linuxsampler-imis: no restrictions at all; you should still give Music Mayor
  and the University of Iowa credit :)

- linuxsampler-maestro: only CC-BY-NC (choice "c") may be used; credit the
  author Mats Helgesson appropriately, of course

- linuxsampler-pleyelp190: only the CC licenses (choice "c" or "d") may be
  used; credit the author Nikko as described on
  http://tickets.nikkoid.com/knowledgebase.php?article=23

- linuxsampler-salamander: only the CC licenses (choice "c" or "d") may be
  used; credit the author Alexander Holm appropriately, of course

- linuxsampler-steinwayc: only the CC licenses (choice "c" or "d") may be
  used; credit the author Nikko as described on
  http://tickets.nikkoid.com/knowledgebase.php?article=23

- linuxsampler-tinypiano: only the CC licenses (choice "c" or "d") may be used;
  credit Signal Experiments (http://sig-ex.com/) appropriately, of course.

- timidity-freepats: no restrictions at all; you should still give the Freepats
  Project credit :)
